genresAdvancedInfo.name: totalism
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Totalism is a contemporary classical music genre that emerged in the late 20th century. It is characterized by its complex and intricate compositions, often featuring repetitive patterns and minimalist elements. Totalism is experimental in nature, pushing the boundaries of traditional classical music.
